addDefaultModules

protected void addDefaultModules(java.util.Collection<java.lang.Class<? extends IFloodlightModule>> userModules)
Adds default modules to the list of modules to load. This is done in order to avoid the module loader throwing errors about duplicate modules and neither one is specified by the user.

Parameters:
userModules - The list of user specified modules to add to.

setupModules

public void setupModules(java.util.Collection<java.lang.Class<? extends IFloodlightModule>> modules,

Sets up all modules and their dependencies.

Parameters:
modules - The list of modules that the user wants to load.
mockedServices - The list of services that will be mocked. Any module that provides this service will not be loaded.
